1. Each PBI will have its own title that uniquely identifies from other PBI. 
2. Each PBI (Product Backlog Items) must be written as user stories in the format of: As a player, I want to [feature] so I can [reason].
3. The PBIs are estimated in story points that are feasible and can be comfortably be completed in one sprint. 
4. Each PBI can be worked on without it dependent on another PBI.
5. PBI dependencies are identified, if any. 
6. A clear acceptance criteria is defined, and testable for each PBI.
